Apt	Aptorii demon bound to Kalam Mekhar; rescues thirteen hundred crucified Malazan children, merges with the blind boy Panek, and shadows Kalam through the Imperial Warren while tearing apart the Semk-bound warrior that Pearl confronts.
Baudin	Companion to Felisin Paran and Heboric after the Cull; described as huge and bestial, with small narrow-set eyes and a thuglike appearance, yet he shows surprising knowledge of the Malazan Empire.
Beneth	Korelri slave who rises to crime lord at Skullcup on Otataral Island; plays both sides with Commandant Sawark, keeps Felisin as addict and lover, and is finally killed by Baudin during the rebellion.
Blistig	Commander of the Aren Guard left to hold the city while Coltaine marched; resentful of Pormqual’s indolence yet loyal to the Empire, he endures the siege as the Chain of Dogs collapses at the gates.
Coltaine	Wickan Fist of the Malazan 7th Army, crow-cloaked cavalry commander who forges the Chain of Dogs escorting tens of thousands of refugees from Hissar across Seven Cities to Aren with relentless tactical ingenuity and brutal discipline.
Duiker	Imperial Historian from Dal Hon assigned to Coltaine’s 7th; veteran soldier-turned-chronicler who documents the Chain of Dogs from Hissar to Aren, riding with the column and fighting when needed.
Felisin Paran|Felisin	Youngest Paran sister of house Paran, sister of Ganoes and Tavore, often described as too soft for this world.
Heboric Light Touch|Heboric	Former High Priest of Fener and an exiled historian, toad-like and bald, his body covered in Fener tattoos and his hands long since severed.
Icarium	Half-Jaghut wanderer of immense but forgotten destructive power; travels Seven Cities with Mappo seeking his lost past while drawn toward the Path of Hands convergence.<br><br> <i>"I admit, Mappo, I feel close this time. Very close." (Icarium, seeking his past)</i>
Iskaral Pust|Iskaral|Pust	Madcap High Priest of Shadow at Tremorlor; duplicitous schemer serving Shadowthrone, guides Icarium and Mappo through the Azath while muttering to his mule and spying via his wives’ coterie.
Kamist Reloe|Kamist|Reloe	Gaunt High Mage of the Army of the Apocalypse, thought dead in Raraku but revealed leading rebel hosts; constructs the ramp at P’atha, hurls sorcery at the Chain of Dogs, yet is repeatedly outmaneuvered by Coltaine’s Wickans.
Keneb	Pragmatic former Malazan captain demoted to supply officer; joins Coltaine’s march, keeps the refugee train moving, and later commands within the battered column.
Korbolo Dom|Dom	A High Fist of the Malazan Empire, he was a half-blood Napan with shaved, dusty blue skin covered in scars. He turned against the Malazan Empire, joining the rebellion in Seven Cities and leading the Whirlwind's warriors. His decision to become a renegade stemmed from his ambition and perceived slight when Coltaine was given command of the 7th army over him, as Dom was considered too bloodthirsty to lead.<br>
Kulp	Squat, white-haired Meanas cadre mage of the 7th; ferries to Skullcup to extract Heboric, survives the Silanda and an undead dragon, then is consumed by the D’ivers Gryllen after safeguarding Felisin’s band in Raraku.
Leoman of the Flails|Leoman	Sha'ik’s chief bodyguard and battlefield commander; famed for twin flails and desert-honed discipline, he orchestrates rebel maneuvers around Raraku and survives Coltaine’s pursuit.
List	Young Wickan-trained corporal of the 7th Army; serves under Bult and Nil, conveying orders and witnessing the attrition of the Chain of Dogs.
Lostara Yil|Lostara|Yil	Pardu-born Red Blades captain with tattooed skin and wide black eyes; sent from Ehrlitan to hunt Kalam, partners uneasily with Claw agent Pearl through the Imperial Warren, and is seized in Aren amid suspicions of treason.
Mallick Rel|Mallick|Rel	Jhistal priest and scheming advisor to High Fist Pormqual; manipulates Seven Cities politics, quietly supports the rebellion, and later betrays Pormqual to Korbolo Dom.
Mappo Runt|Mappo|Runt	Trell guardian sworn to keep Icarium’s past suppressed; loyal, grief-haunted companion who steers Icarium away from triggers while traversing Seven Cities and the Azath at Tremorlor.
Minala	Keneb’s widowed sister-in-law travelling with her children on the Chain of Dogs; sharp-tongued and resilient, she forms a strained alliance with Duiker and the Wickans.
Nil	Wickan warlock twin, alongside Nether; channels earth spirits to shield the Chain of Dogs and coordinates with Sormo E’nath under Coltaine.
Nether	Young Wickan warlock twin who partners Nil; her healing and spirit-work sustain refugees and soldiers through the march’s attrition.
Pearl	A Mockra mage of the Claw, tall, dark-skinned and sharply handsome with green eyes, favouring loose green silks and rings of glittering green gems; one-quarter Tiste Andii, he carried hidden throwing stars on his chest-belt and knives beneath his half-cloak, operated under the alias Salk Elan, and was once Topper's favoured lieutenant. He escorted Lostara Yil through the Imperial Warren in the hunt for Kalam.
Pella	Skullcup guard and soldier who guides Felisin’s group through the Otataral camp upheaval before meeting his end in the desert.
Ryllandaras	Soletaken and D’ivers known as the White Jackal; shifts between giant man-jackal and a pack of wolves, notorious predator along the Path of Hands and feared curse of Quon and the Seven Cities hinterlands.
Sawark	Commandant of Skullcup on Otataral Island; brutal overseer complicit in abuses, toppled during the Whirlwind revolt as the mines erupt in chaos.
Sha'ik	The title for the chosen one of the Whirlwind Goddess, also known as the "Hand of Dryjhna" and "Seeress of the Apocalypse." The original Sha'ik was a prophetess and leader of the Whirlwind rebellion in the Holy Desert Raraku. She was a small, dark-haired woman whose appearance reflected her harsh desert life.
Sormo E'nath|Sormo|E'nath	Reborn Wickan warlock, outwardly a lanky boy in a goat-cowled cloak yet carrying the souls of elder warlocks; leads Nil and Nether in support of Coltaine, communes with land-spirits to counter Kamist Reloe, and dies under arrows at Vathar Crossing.
Tavore Paran|Tavore	Second child of house Paran, sister to Ganoes and Felisin.<br><br> <i>"Command does not come from consensus. I deliver the orders and my officers are to obey them. They should be relieved that is the case, for all responsibility lies with me and me alone. No-one else shall have to answer to the empress."</i>
Toblakai	Huge, taciturn warrior guarding Sha'ik’s camp; a soletaken-linked giant on the Path of Hands, later revealed as Karsa Orlong, though in this tale known only by the Toblakai name.
